Me and my girlfriend came to this restaurant because we heard they have vegan and vegetarian options. They do! The rice and beans are vegan and they also have vegan sour cream and cheese. Their vegan options are Flor de calabaza (zucchini flower), huitlacoche (corn smut), hongos (mushrooms) and nopales (cactus) you can make burritos, tacos, quesadillas, gorditas, or sopes with these options and maybe more! Alejandra, our server, is vegan and daughter of the owner and she is trying to get mock meats on the menu soon. She was very helpful! Order aguas de jamaica or tamarindo with yout meal it goes wonderfully. The salsas are also made fresh and are delicious and spicy.

I haven't write about restaurants in a while.. if I'm do it it's because I really do have something to share.. little context first. We found this place because I was looking for a book in Spanish, Mein Kampf by Adolf Hitler; this  political times and changes reminds me the poor Austria back then early 20'.. so there is this Lozano branch, Chicago public library wich has the biggest Spanish collection around here..after getting all our books for the month we decide to have lunch around there, we Google the best option and this little place pops out. " Best mole de Mayo.." they claim.  And that's so true.. it was week day.. we found it exquisite. Then we decide to come back on weekends.. to try all the weekend menu. Oh my God.. everything is delicious from breakfast, caldos, the green pozole.. oh my.. I tried the cabrito.. oh man. It's close to Monterrey. The salsa it's delicious. My favorite .. chilaquiles Verdes with meat.. and Cafe de olla.. the best..  Very kind people, Doña Gaby.. the best fine lady who attends you with patient, kindness, always smiling, and I don't know this other guy's name yet,  with tattoos, the same, very fine person. I'm glad we found this little and quiet place over Blue Island.  If this is your first time, give it a try.. if you don't speak Spanish, no worries, nobody is perfect. Lol. Menu is easy to understand.  My two cents.
